<!-- REAL-ESRGAN TUTORIAL -->
< This note was edited by "NIHIL Project" and is based on the official GitHub page "xinntao" about Real-ESRGAN. More detailed instructions can be found on the official page at the following link: https://github.com/xinntao/Real-ESRGAN >

1. Place the images in the same folder level as your .exe file.

2. [cd] To where your file is located on your command prompt, and you can simply run the following command: (replace the () with the corresponding name:
realesrgan-ncnn-vulkan.exe -i (input_image) -o (output.png)

example (default):
	< realesrgan-ncnn-vulkan.exe -i Photo.jpg -o PhotoHD.png >

3. You can use the -n argument for other models:
realesrgan-ncnn-vulkan.exe -i (input_image) -o (output.png) -n (model_name)

example (take the original photo details, but the results are still a little blurry):
	< realesrgan-ncnn-vulkan.exe -i Photo.jpg -o PhotoHD.png -n realesrnet-x4plus >
example (better for anime/cartoons):
	< realesrgan-ncnn-vulkan.exe -i Photo.jpg -o PhotoHD.png -n realesrgan-x4plus-anime >

4. You can enhance the quality of multiple photos/images in a specific folder at the same time:
realesrgan-ncnn-vulkan.exe -i (input_folder) -o (output_folder)

example (with default model):
	< realesrgan-ncnn-vulkan.exe -i lowres -o highres >
example (with model):
	< realesrgan-ncnn-vulkan.exe -i lowres -o highres -n realesrnet-x4plus > or
	< realesrgan-ncnn-vulkan.exe -i lowres -o highres -n realesrgan-x4plus-anime >
	
